    "message_1": "Suppose you have been given the following data set: \n\n| x   | y     |\n| --- | ----- |\n| -1  | 1     |\n| 0   | 0.5   |\n| 1   | -0.5  |\n| 2   | -3    |\n| 3   | -8.5  |\n| 4   | -18.5 |\n\nUsing the Lagrange interpolating polynomial, find the value of y when x = 1.5.",
    "message_2": "To find the value of y when x = 1.5 using the Lagrange interpolating polynomial, we can use the following formula:\n\nL(x) = y0 * l0(x) + y1 * l1(x) + y2 * l2(x) + ... + yn * ln(x)\n\nwhere L(x) is the Lagrange polynomial, y0, y1, ..., yn are the given y values, and l0(x), l1(x), ..., ln(x) are the Lagrange basis polynomials defined as:\n\nli(x) = Π((x - xj) / (xi - xj)) for j = 0, 1, ..., n and j ≠ i\n\nFor the given data set, we have 6 points, so n = 5. Let's calculate the Lagrange basis polynomials for x = 1.5:\n\nl0(1.5) = ((1.5 - 0) * (1.5 - 1) * (1.5 - 2) * (1.5 - 3) * (1.5 - 4)) / ((-1 - 0) * (-1 - 1) * (-1 - 2) * (-1 - 3) * (-1 - 4)) = 0.075\nl1(1.5) = ((1.5 + 1) * (1.5 - 1) * (1.5 - 2) * (1.5 - 3) * (1.5 - 4)) / ((0 + 1) * (0 - 1) * (0 - 2) * (0 - 3) * (0 - 4)) = -0.25\nl2(1.5) = ((1.5 + 1) * (1.5 - 0) * (1.5 - 2) * (1.5 - 3) * (1.5 - 4)) / ((1 + 1) * (1 - 0) * (1 - 2) * (1 - 3) * (1 - 4)) = 0.5625\nl3(1.5) = ((1.5 + 1) * (1.5 - 0) * (1.5 - 1) * (1.5 - 3) * (1.5 - 4)) / ((2 + 1) * (2 - 0) * (2 - 1) * (2 - 3) * (2 - 4)) = -0.375\nl4(1.5) = ((1.5 + 1) * (1.5 - 0) * (1.5 - 1) * (1.5 - 2) * (1.5 - 4)) / ((3 + 1) * (3 - 0) * (3 - 1) * (3 - 2) * (3 - 4)) = 0.1875\nl5(1.5) = ((1.5 + 1) * (1.5 - 0) * (1.5 - 1) * (1.5 - 2) * (1.5 - 3)) / ((4 + 1) * (4 - 0) * (4 - 1) * (4 - 2) * (4 - 3)) = -0.03125\n\nNow, we can calculate L(1.5):\n\nL(1.5) = 1 * 0.075 + 0.5 * (-0.25) + (-0.5) * 0.5625 + (-3) * (-0.375) + (-8.5) * 0.1875 + (-18.5) * (-0.03125) = 0.075 - 0.125 - 0.28125 + 1.125 + 1.59375 + 0.578125 = 2.965625\n\nSo, the value of y when x = 1.5 using the Lagrange interpolating polynomial is approximately 2.965625."
